3583/// The cached properties of a type.
3584class CachedProperties {
3585 Linkage L;
3586 bool local;
3587
3588public:
3589 CachedProperties(Linkage L, bool local) : L(L), local(local) {}
3590
3591 Linkage getLinkage() const { return L; }
3592 bool hasLocalOrUnnamedType() const { return local; }
3593
3594 friend CachedProperties merge(CachedProperties L, CachedProperties R) {
3595 Linkage MergedLinkage = minLinkage(L.L, R.L);
3596 return CachedProperties(MergedLinkage,
3597 L.hasLocalOrUnnamedType() | R.hasLocalOrUnnamedType());
3598 }
3599};
3600
3601} // namespace
3602
3603static CachedProperties computeCachedProperties(const Type *T);
3604
3605namespace clang {
3606
3607/// The type-property cache. This is templated so as to be
3608/// instantiated at an internal type to prevent unnecessary symbol
3609/// leakage.
3610template <class Private> class TypePropertyCache {
3611public:
3612 static CachedProperties get(QualType T) {
3613 return get(T.getTypePtr());
3614 }
3615
3616 static CachedProperties get(const Type *T) {
3617 ensure(T);
3618 return CachedProperties(T->TypeBits.getLinkage(),
3619 T->TypeBits.hasLocalOrUnnamedType());
3620 }
3621
3622 static void ensure(const Type *T) {
3623 // If the cache is valid, we're okay.
3624 if (T->TypeBits.isCacheValid()) return;
3625
3626 // If this type is non-canonical, ask its canonical type for the
3627 // relevant information.
3628 if (!T->isCanonicalUnqualified()) {
3629 const Type *CT = T->getCanonicalTypeInternal().getTypePtr();
3630 ensure(CT);
3631 T->TypeBits.CacheValid = true;
3632 T->TypeBits.CachedLinkage = CT->TypeBits.CachedLinkage;
3633 T->TypeBits.CachedLocalOrUnnamed = CT->TypeBits.CachedLocalOrUnnamed;
3634 return;
3635 }
3636
3637 // Compute the cached properties and then set the cache.
3638 CachedProperties Result = computeCachedProperties(T);
3639 T->TypeBits.CacheValid = true;
3640 T->TypeBits.CachedLinkage = Result.getLinkage();
3641 T->TypeBits.CachedLocalOrUnnamed = Result.hasLocalOrUnnamedType();
3642 }
3643};
3644
3645} // namespace clang

3647// Instantiate the friend template at a private class. In a
3648// reasonable implementation, these symbols will be internal.
3649// It is terrible that this is the best way to accomplish this.
3650namespace {
3651
3652class Private {};
3653
3654} // namespace

3656using Cache = TypePropertyCache<Private>;
3657
3658static CachedProperties computeCachedProperties(const Type *T) {
3659 switch (T->getTypeClass()) {
3660#define TYPE(Class,Base)
3661#define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class,Base) case Type::Class:
3662#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
3663 llvm_unreachable("didn't expect a non-canonical type here");
3664
3665#define TYPE(Class,Base)
3666#define DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class,Base) case Type::Class:
3667#define NON_CANONICAL_UNLESS_DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class,Base) case Type::Class:
3668#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
3669 // Treat instantiation-dependent types as external.
3670 assert(T->isInstantiationDependentType());
3671 return CachedProperties(ExternalLinkage, false);
3672
3673 case Type::Auto:
3674 case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization:
3675 // Give non-deduced 'auto' types external linkage. We should only see them
3676 // here in error recovery.
3677 return CachedProperties(ExternalLinkage, false);
3678
3679 case Type::Builtin:
3680 // C++ [basic.link]p8:
3681 // A type is said to have linkage if and only if:
3682 // - it is a fundamental type (3.9.1); or
3683 return CachedProperties(ExternalLinkage, false);
3684
3685 case Type::Record:
3686 case Type::Enum: {
3687 const TagDecl *Tag = cast<TagType>(T)->getDecl();
3688
3689 // C++ [basic.link]p8:
3690 // - it is a class or enumeration type that is named (or has a name
3691 // for linkage purposes (7.1.3)) and the name has linkage; or
3692 // - it is a specialization of a class template (14); or
3693 Linkage L = Tag->getLinkageInternal();
3694 bool IsLocalOrUnnamed =
3695 Tag->getDeclContext()->isFunctionOrMethod() ||
3696 !Tag->hasNameForLinkage();
3697 return CachedProperties(L, IsLocalOrUnnamed);
3698 }
3699
3700 // C++ [basic.link]p8:
3701 // - it is a compound type (3.9.2) other than a class or enumeration,
3702 // compounded exclusively from types that have linkage; or
3703 case Type::Complex:
3704 return Cache::get(cast<ComplexType>(T)->getElementType());
3705 case Type::Pointer:
3706 return Cache::get(cast<PointerType>(T)->getPointeeType());
3707 case Type::BlockPointer:
3708 return Cache::get(cast<BlockPointerType>(T)->getPointeeType());
3709 case Type::LValueReference:
3710 case Type::RValueReference:
3711 return Cache::get(cast<ReferenceType>(T)->getPointeeType());
3712 case Type::MemberPointer: {
3713 const auto *MPT = cast<MemberPointerType>(T);
3714 return merge(Cache::get(MPT->getClass()),
3715 Cache::get(MPT->getPointeeType()));
3716 }
3717 case Type::ConstantArray:
3718 case Type::IncompleteArray:
3719 case Type::VariableArray:
3720 return Cache::get(cast<ArrayType>(T)->getElementType());
3721 case Type::Vector:
3722 case Type::ExtVector:
3723 return Cache::get(cast<VectorType>(T)->getElementType());
3724 case Type::FunctionNoProto:
3725 return Cache::get(cast<FunctionType>(T)->getReturnType());
3726 case Type::FunctionProto: {
3727 const auto *FPT = cast<FunctionProtoType>(T);
3728 CachedProperties result = Cache::get(FPT->getReturnType());
3729 for (const auto &ai : FPT->param_types())
3730 result = merge(result, Cache::get(ai));
3731 return result;
3732 }
3733 case Type::ObjCInterface: {
3734 Linkage L = cast<ObjCInterfaceType>(T)->getDecl()->getLinkageInternal();
3735 return CachedProperties(L, false);
3736 }
3737 case Type::ObjCObject:
3738 return Cache::get(cast<ObjCObjectType>(T)->getBaseType());
3739 case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
3740 return Cache::get(cast<ObjCObjectPointerType>(T)->getPointeeType());
3741 case Type::Atomic:
3742 return Cache::get(cast<AtomicType>(T)->getValueType());
3743 case Type::Pipe:
3744 return Cache::get(cast<PipeType>(T)->getElementType());
3745 }
3746
3747 llvm_unreachable("unhandled type class");
3748}

3752 Cache::ensure(this);
3753 return TypeBits.getLinkage();
3754}

3757 Cache::ensure(this);

3761LinkageInfo LinkageComputer::computeTypeLinkageInfo(const Type *T) {
3762 switch (T->getTypeClass()) {
3763#define TYPE(Class,Base)
3764#define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class,Base) case Type::Class:
3765#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
3766 llvm_unreachable("didn't expect a non-canonical type here");
3767
3768#define TYPE(Class,Base)
3769#define DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class,Base) case Type::Class:
3770#define NON_CANONICAL_UNLESS_DEPENDENT_TYPE(Class,Base) case Type::Class:
3771#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
3772 // Treat instantiation-dependent types as external.
3773 assert(T->isInstantiationDependentType());
3774 return LinkageInfo::external();
3775
3776 case Type::Builtin:
3777 return LinkageInfo::external();
3778
3779 case Type::Auto:
3780 case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization:
3781 return LinkageInfo::external();
3782
3783 case Type::Record:
3784 case Type::Enum:
3785 return getDeclLinkageAndVisibility(cast<TagType>(T)->getDecl());
3786
3787 case Type::Complex:
3788 return computeTypeLinkageInfo(cast<ComplexType>(T)->getElementType());
3789 case Type::Pointer:
3790 return computeTypeLinkageInfo(cast<PointerType>(T)->getPointeeType());
3791 case Type::BlockPointer:
3792 return computeTypeLinkageInfo(cast<BlockPointerType>(T)->getPointeeType());
3793 case Type::LValueReference:
3794 case Type::RValueReference:
3795 return computeTypeLinkageInfo(cast<ReferenceType>(T)->getPointeeType());
3796 case Type::MemberPointer: {
3797 const auto *MPT = cast<MemberPointerType>(T);
3798 LinkageInfo LV = computeTypeLinkageInfo(MPT->getClass());
3799 LV.merge(computeTypeLinkageInfo(MPT->getPointeeType()));
3800 return LV;
3801 }
3802 case Type::ConstantArray:
3803 case Type::IncompleteArray:
3804 case Type::VariableArray:
3805 return computeTypeLinkageInfo(cast<ArrayType>(T)->getElementType());
3806 case Type::Vector:
3807 case Type::ExtVector:
3808 return computeTypeLinkageInfo(cast<VectorType>(T)->getElementType());
3809 case Type::FunctionNoProto:
3810 return computeTypeLinkageInfo(cast<FunctionType>(T)->getReturnType());
3811 case Type::FunctionProto: {
3812 const auto *FPT = cast<FunctionProtoType>(T);
3813 LinkageInfo LV = computeTypeLinkageInfo(FPT->getReturnType());
3814 for (const auto &ai : FPT->param_types())
3815 LV.merge(computeTypeLinkageInfo(ai));
3816 return LV;
3817 }
3818 case Type::ObjCInterface:
3819 return getDeclLinkageAndVisibility(cast<ObjCInterfaceType>(T)->getDecl());
3820 case Type::ObjCObject:
3821 return computeTypeLinkageInfo(cast<ObjCObjectType>(T)->getBaseType());
3822 case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
3823 return computeTypeLinkageInfo(
3824 cast<ObjCObjectPointerType>(T)->getPointeeType());
3825 case Type::Atomic:
3826 return computeTypeLinkageInfo(cast<AtomicType>(T)->getValueType());
3827 case Type::Pipe:
3828 return computeTypeLinkageInfo(cast<PipeType>(T)->getElementType());
3829 }
3830
3831 llvm_unreachable("unhandled type class");
3832}

3834bool Type::isLinkageValid() const {
3835 if (!TypeBits.isCacheValid())
3836 return true;
3837
3838 Linkage L = LinkageComputer{}
3839 .computeTypeLinkageInfo(getCanonicalTypeInternal())
3840 .getLinkage();
3841 return L == TypeBits.getLinkage();
3842}

3844LinkageInfo LinkageComputer::getTypeLinkageAndVisibility(const Type *T) {
3845 if (!T->isCanonicalUnqualified())
3846 return computeTypeLinkageInfo(T->getCanonicalTypeInternal());
3847
3848 LinkageInfo LV = computeTypeLinkageInfo(T);
3849 assert(LV.getLinkage() == T->getLinkage());
3850 return LV;
3851}

3853LinkageInfo Type::getLinkageAndVisibility() const {
3854 return LinkageComputer{}.getTypeLinkageAndVisibility(this);

3857Optional<NullabilityKind>
3858Type::getNullability(const ASTContext &Context) const {
3859 QualType Type(this, 0);
3860 while (const auto *AT = Type->getAs<AttributedType>()) {
3861 // Check whether this is an attributed type with nullability
3862 // information.
3863 if (auto Nullability = AT->getImmediateNullability())
3864 return Nullability;
3865
3866 Type = AT->getEquivalentType();
3867 }
3868 return None;
3869}
3870
3871bool Type::canHaveNullability(bool ResultIfUnknown) const {
3872 QualType type = getCanonicalTypeInternal();
3873
3874 switch (type->getTypeClass()) {
3875 // We'll only see canonical types here.
3876#define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class, Parent) \
3877 case Type::Class: \
3878 llvm_unreachable("non-canonical type");
3879#define TYPE(Class, Parent)
3880#include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.def"
3881
3882 // Pointer types.
3883 case Type::Pointer:
3884 case Type::BlockPointer:
3885 case Type::MemberPointer:
3886 case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
3887 return true;
3888
3889 // Dependent types that could instantiate to pointer types.
3890 case Type::UnresolvedUsing:
3891 case Type::TypeOfExpr:
3892 case Type::TypeOf:
3893 case Type::Decltype:
3894 case Type::UnaryTransform:
3895 case Type::TemplateTypeParm:
3896 case Type::SubstTemplateTypeParmPack:
3897 case Type::DependentName:
3898 case Type::DependentTemplateSpecialization:
3899 case Type::Auto:
3900 return ResultIfUnknown;
3901
3902 // Dependent template specializations can instantiate to pointer
3903 // types unless they're known to be specializations of a class
3904 // template.
3905 case Type::TemplateSpecialization:
3906 if (TemplateDecl *templateDecl
3907 = cast<TemplateSpecializationType>(type.getTypePtr())
3908 ->getTemplateName().getAsTemplateDecl()) {
3909 if (isa<ClassTemplateDecl>(templateDecl))
3910 return false;
3911 }
3912 return ResultIfUnknown;
3913
3914 case Type::Builtin:
3915 switch (cast<BuiltinType>(type.getTypePtr())->getKind()) {
3916 // Signed, unsigned, and floating-point types cannot have nullability.
3917#define SIGNED_TYPE(Id, SingletonId) case BuiltinType::Id:
3918#define UNSIGNED_TYPE(Id, SingletonId) case BuiltinType::Id:
3919#define FLOATING_TYPE(Id, SingletonId) case BuiltinType::Id:
3920#define BUILTIN_TYPE(Id, SingletonId)
3921#include "clang/AST/BuiltinTypes.def"
3922 return false;
3923
3924 // Dependent types that could instantiate to a pointer type.
3925 case BuiltinType::Dependent:
3926 case BuiltinType::Overload:
3927 case BuiltinType::BoundMember:
3928 case BuiltinType::PseudoObject:
3929 case BuiltinType::UnknownAny:
3930 case BuiltinType::ARCUnbridgedCast:
3931 return ResultIfUnknown;
3932
3933 case BuiltinType::Void:
3934 case BuiltinType::ObjCId:
3935 case BuiltinType::ObjCClass:
3936 case BuiltinType::ObjCSel:
3937#define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
3938 case BuiltinType::Id:
3939#include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
3940#define EXT_OPAQUE_TYPE(ExtType, Id, Ext) \
3941 case BuiltinType::Id:
3942#include "clang/Basic/OpenCLExtensionTypes.def"
3943 case BuiltinType::OCLSampler:
3944 case BuiltinType::OCLEvent:
3945 case BuiltinType::OCLClkEvent:
3946 case BuiltinType::OCLQueue:
3947 case BuiltinType::OCLReserveID:
3948 case BuiltinType::BuiltinFn:
3949 case BuiltinType::NullPtr:
3950 case BuiltinType::OMPArraySection:
3951 return false;
3952 }
3953 llvm_unreachable("unknown builtin type");
3954
3955 // Non-pointer types.
3956 case Type::Complex:
3957 case Type::LValueReference:
3958 case Type::RValueReference:
3959 case Type::ConstantArray:
3960 case Type::IncompleteArray:
3961 case Type::VariableArray:
3962 case Type::DependentSizedArray:
3963 case Type::DependentVector:
3964 case Type::DependentSizedExtVector:
3965 case Type::Vector:
3966 case Type::ExtVector:
3967 case Type::DependentAddressSpace:
3968 case Type::FunctionProto:
3969 case Type::FunctionNoProto:
3970 case Type::Record:
3971 case Type::DeducedTemplateSpecialization:
3972 case Type::Enum:
3973 case Type::InjectedClassName:
3974 case Type::PackExpansion:
3975 case Type::ObjCObject:
3976 case Type::ObjCInterface:
3977 case Type::Atomic:
3978 case Type::Pipe:
3979 return false;
3980 }
3981 llvm_unreachable("bad type kind!");
3982}

3984llvm::Optional<NullabilityKind>
3985AttributedType::getImmediateNullability() const {
3986 if (getAttrKind() == attr::TypeNonNull)
3987 return NullabilityKind::NonNull;
3988 if (getAttrKind() == attr::TypeNullable)
3989 return NullabilityKind::Nullable;
3990 if (getAttrKind() == attr::TypeNullUnspecified)
3991 return NullabilityKind::Unspecified;
3992 return None;
3993}

3995Optional<NullabilityKind> AttributedType::stripOuterNullability(QualType &T) {
3996 QualType AttrTy = T;
3997 if (auto MacroTy = dyn_cast<MacroQualifiedType>(T))
3998 AttrTy = MacroTy->getUnderlyingType();
3999
4000 if (auto attributed = dyn_cast<AttributedType>(AttrTy)) {
4001 if (auto nullability = attributed->getImmediateNullability()) {
4002 T = attributed->getModifiedType();
4003 return nullability;
4004 }
4005 }
4006
4007 return None;
4008}

4010bool Type::isBlockCompatibleObjCPointerType(ASTContext &ctx) const {
4011 const auto *objcPtr = getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
4012 if (!objcPtr)
4013 return false;
4014
4015 if (objcPtr->isObjCIdType()) {
4016 // id is always okay.
4017 return true;
4018 }
4019
4020 // Blocks are NSObjects.
4021 if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *iface = objcPtr->getInterfaceDecl()) {
4022 if (iface->getIdentifier() != ctx.getNSObjectName())
4023 return false;
4024
4025 // Continue to check qualifiers, below.
4026 } else if (objcPtr->isObjCQualifiedIdType()) {
4027 // Continue to check qualifiers, below.
4028 } else {
4029 return false;
4030 }
4031
4032 // Check protocol qualifiers.
4033 for (ObjCProtocolDecl *proto : objcPtr->quals()) {
4034 // Blocks conform to NSObject and NSCopying.
4035 if (proto->getIdentifier() != ctx.getNSObjectName() &&
4036 proto->getIdentifier() != ctx.getNSCopyingName())
4037 return false;
4038 }
4039
4040 return true;
4041}

4045 return Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone;
4046 return Qualifiers::OCL_Strong;

4049bool Type::isObjCARCImplicitlyUnretainedType() const {
4050 assert(isObjCLifetimeType() &&
4051 "cannot query implicit lifetime for non-inferrable type");
4052
4053 const Type *canon = getCanonicalTypeInternal().getTypePtr();
4054
4055 // Walk down to the base type. We don't care about qualifiers for this.
4056 while (const auto *array = dyn_cast<ArrayType>(canon))
4057 canon = array->getElementType().getTypePtr();
4058
4059 if (const auto *opt = dyn_cast<ObjCObjectPointerType>(canon)) {
4060 // Class and Class<Protocol> don't require retention.
4061 if (opt->getObjectType()->isObjCClass())
4062 return true;
4063 }
4064
4065 return false;
4066}

4068bool Type::isObjCNSObjectType() const {
4069 const Type *cur = this;
4070 while (true) {
4071 if (const auto *typedefType = dyn_cast<TypedefType>(cur))
4072 return typedefType->getDecl()->hasAttr<ObjCNSObjectAttr>();
4073
4074 // Single-step desugar until we run out of sugar.
4075 QualType next = cur->getLocallyUnqualifiedSingleStepDesugaredType();
4076 if (next.getTypePtr() == cur) return false;
4077 cur = next.getTypePtr();
4078 }
4079}

4083 return typedefType->getDecl()->hasAttr<ObjCIndependentClassAttr>();
4084 return false;

4106/// ARC.

4110 type = array->getElementType().getTypePtr();

4130bool Type::hasSizedVLAType() const {
4131 if (!isVariablyModifiedType()) return false;
4132
4133 if (const auto *ptr = getAs<PointerType>())
4134 return ptr->getPointeeType()->hasSizedVLAType();
4135 if (const auto *ref = getAs<ReferenceType>())
4136 return ref->getPointeeType()->hasSizedVLAType();
4137 if (const ArrayType *arr = getAsArrayTypeUnsafe()) {
4138 if (isa<VariableArrayType>(arr) &&
4139 cast<VariableArrayType>(arr)->getSizeExpr())
4140 return true;
4141
4142 return arr->getElementType()->hasSizedVLAType();
4143 }
4144
4145 return false;
4146}

4148QualType::DestructionKind QualType::isDestructedTypeImpl(QualType type) {
4149 switch (type.getObjCLifetime()) {
4150 case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
4151 case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
4152 case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
4153 break;
4154
4155 case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
4156 return DK_objc_strong_lifetime;
4157 case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
4158 return DK_objc_weak_lifetime;
4159 }
4160
4161 if (const auto *RT =
4162 type->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAs<RecordType>()) {
4163 const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
4164 if (const auto *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
4165 /// Check if this is a C++ object with a non-trivial destructor.
4166 if (CXXRD->hasDefinition() && !CXXRD->hasTrivialDestructor())
4167 return DK_cxx_destructor;
4168 } else {
4169 /// Check if this is a C struct that is non-trivial to destroy or an array
4170 /// that contains such a struct.
4171 if (RD->isNonTrivialToPrimitiveDestroy())
4172 return DK_nontrivial_c_struct;
4173 }
4174 }
4175
4176 return DK_none;
4177}

4180 return getClass()->getAsCXXRecordDecl()->getMostRecentNonInjectedDecl();
4181}
